The endangered giant panda population in China has increased to around 1,590, with a focus on protecting the Qinling pandas due to their smaller numbers.
A blood bank has been established to aid in conservation efforts by collecting and storing blood samples for research.
Recent reports indicate that some pandas are migrating to new areas due to blooming bamboo and food shortages.
Efforts are being made to rescue pandas facing starvation and relocate them to areas with better food sources.
Conservation measures include setting up nature reserves and increasing forest coverage to protect the pandas' habitat.
